# IAM GitHub â€” OAuth Write + SSH Git (SamPrimeaux)

## OAuth connected agents (ChatGPT MCP, in-app)

**`agentsam_github_write`** now uses **`upsert_file`**:

| Case | What to pass |
|------|----------------|
| **New file** | `path`, `content`, `message`, `repo` â€” **omit `sha`** |
| **Update existing** | Same + optional `sha` from prior `agentsam_github_read` |

Do **not** pass `sha: ""` â€” omit the field entirely for creates.

**Read/discover:** `agentsam_github_read`, `agentsam_github_repo_list`

**Not for `agentsam_github_write`:** multi-file edits, binary assets, scaffolds, build/commit/push â†’ `agentsam_terminal_local` + git over SSH.

## Terminal git â€” all Sam repos (Sam / `ws_inneranimalmedia`)

Install **`gh` + git credential helper** on both PTY hosts:

```bash
# Sam (platform): Mac + shared GCP iam-tunnel
./scripts/install-terminal-github-cli.sh --prompt-token

# Connor (or any non-Sam operator): local machine only, your PAT, never SamPrimeaux
./scripts/install-terminal-github-cli-connor.sh
```

Connor's token is stored in `~/.config/iam/github.env`, not repo `.env.cloudflare`.

SSH push works without `gh`; `gh` adds `gh pr create`, HTTPS clone fallback, etc.

| Pattern | Remote |
|---------|--------|
| Any `SamPrimeaux/REPO` | `git@github.com:SamPrimeaux/REPO.git` |
| `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server` only | `git@github.com-inneranimal-mcp:SamPrimeaux/inneranimalmedia-mcp-server.git` |

```bash
git clone git@github.com:SamPrimeaux/YOUR-REPO.git
# ... edit multiple files ...
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: scaffold" && git push origin HEAD
```

SSH host aliases on PTY: `github.com`, `github-inneranimal`, `github.com-inneranimal-mcp`, `github.com-agentsam`.

## HTTPS push 403 â†’ SSH recovery

When terminal output shows permission denied or 403 on `https://github.com/...` push:

```bash
git remote -v
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:OWNER/REPO.git
git push origin HEAD
```

Only when the workspace/user is authorized for SSH. Prefer SSH remotes on PTY from the start.

## Node optional binding failures

If build fails with missing native bindings (`Cannot find native binding`, `@rolldown/binding-*`):

```bash
npm i && npm run build
```

Retry before rewriting application source.

